If mfold is used in work that is published, please cite:

1. For the "classic" article on the suboptimal algorithm:

M. Zuker 
On Finding All Suboptimal Foldings of an RNA Molecule. 
Science 244, 48-52 (1989) 

2. The most up-to-date reference on the method:

M. Zuker, D.H. Mathews & D.H. Turner 
Algorithms and Thermodynamics for RNA Secondary Structure Prediction:
A Practical Guide 
in RNA Biochemistry and Biotechnology, J. Barciszewski & B.F.C. Clark,
eds., NATO ASI Series, Kluwer Academic Publishers, (1999) 

3. If you use version 2.3 free energy rules for folding RNA:

A.E. Walter, D.H. Turner, J. Kim, M.H. Lyttle, P. Müller, D.H. Mathews
& M. Zuker 
Coaxial stacking of helixes enhances binding of oligoribonucleotides
and improves predictions of RNA folding. 
Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA 91, 9218-9222 (1994) 

4. If you fold RNA using the latest version 3.1 free energies:

D.H. Mathews, J. Sabina, M. Zuker & D.H. Turner 
Expanded Sequence Dependence of Thermodynamic Parameters Provides
Robust Prediction of RNA Secondary Structure 
J. Mol. Biol. (in press) (1999) 

5. If you are folding DNA:

J.Jr SantaLucia
"A unified view of polymer, dumbbell, and oligonucleotide DNA 
nearest-neighbor thermodynamics."
Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA 95, 1460-1465 (1998)

